  "prompt_text": "Write a function to find all permutations of a string. What is the time complexity?",
  "response_text": "**Permutations of a String Function**\n=====================================\n\nHere's a Python function to find all permutations of a given string using recursion.\n\n```python\ndef get_permutations(s):\n    \"\"\"\n    Returns all permutations of a given string.\n\n    Args:\n        s (str): The input string.\n\n    Returns:\n        list: A list of all permutations of the input string.\n    \"\"\"\n    # Base case: if the string is empty or has only one character, return it as the only permutation\n    if len(s) <= 1:\n        return [s]\n\n    # Initialize an empty list to store the permutations\n    permutations = []\n\n    # For each character in the string\n    for i, char in enumerate(s):\n        # Remove the character from the string\n        remaining_string = s[:i] + s[i + 1:]\n\n        # Generate all permutations of the remaining string\n        for p in get_permutations(remaining_string):\n            # Add the removed character to the beginning of each permutation\n            permutations.append(char + p)\n\n    return permutations\n\n# Example usage:\nprint(get_permutations('abc'))\n```\n\n**Time Complexity Analysis**\n---------------------------\n\nThe time complexity of this function is O(n*n!), where n is the length of the input string. This is because for each character in the string, we are generating n! permutations of the remaining string. The factorial function grows very rapidly, so this function is not efficient for large input strings.\n\n**Space Complexity**\n-------------------\n\nThe space complexity of this function is O(n*n!), as we are storing all permutations in memory.\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 8\nV (Verbal Fluency): 9\nG (Goal Directedness): 9\nP (Pattern Recognition): 8\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 8\nQ (Query Interpretation): 9\nC (Contextual Awareness): 8\nY (Affective Modeling): 6\nF (Flexibility): 8\nD (Depth of Processing): 8\n---END RATINGS---",
